title: Chelsea only English team in Uefa’s top ten clubs as the coefficient rankings are released
text:
Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) Comments UEFA have released their latest coefficient rankings and Chelsea remain the English club in Europe’s top ten. 
The club stayed above 11th placed Arsenal despite not competing in Europe this season. Getty Images Chelsea remain one of Europe’s top ten clubs 
Real Madrid are Europe’s top club with Bayern Munich remaining above Barcelona in second. 
Keep up to date with ALL the Chelsea news, gossip, transfers and goals on our club page plus fixtures, results and live match commentary 
Arsenal fans have been dismayed at Arsene Wenger’s side’s European displays over the previous few years, in particular last week’s 5-1 hammering at Bayern. 
But the Gunners’ ability to consistently get out of their Champions League group makes them the second best English club in Uefa’s rankings . 
Manchester City come in 13th, ahead of rivals United but one place below Porto, while the Red Devils are in 19th below Zenit St Petersburg. AP:Associated Press Arsenal remain Europe’s 11th best team despite being thumped by Bayern Munich PA:Press Association Pep Guardiola’s Man City are the 13th best team in Europe PA:Press Association Man United come in 19th, below City and Zenit St Petersburg Reuters And Jurgen Klopp’s Liverpool have moved below Ajax, down to 32nd Reuters Only Hull City have gone up in Uefa’s rankings 
The latest coefficient rankings are particularly disappointing for Liverpool, who moved down to 32nd below Ajax. 
Leicester and West Ham also move down in the rankings with the Foxes dropping to 62nd, below Gent, and the Hammers dropping to 110th, behind their Europa League conquerors FC Astra Giurgiu. 
Only one English team has moved up in the Uefa rankings. Bayern Munich players celebrate on the pitch after Arsenal Champions League rout 
Hull City are now 120th, above Partizan Belgrade, despite only playing two European ties in their history. 
The Tigers competed in the Europa League two years ago, beating AS Trencin of Slovakia, but then losing to KSC Lokeren of Belgium.
